A man who participated in the Mandela Day Marathon in Howick on Sunday has died, organisers have said. The man collapsed a few metres before the finish line of the 21km race, organisers said. He cannot be named until his next of kin are informed. READ:Mandela Day Marathon back on track after threat resolved The man was immediately treated by a doctor and paramedics, before being taken to to hospital where he was declared dead, the KwaZulu-Natal Department of Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs said in a statement. "It is for the first time that the Mandela Day Marathon experiences such a tragic loss of life in it’s seven-year history," spokesperson Lennox Mabaso said. Organisers are in touch with the family of the deceased and have expressed condolences to the family. GET THE NEWS at your fingertips and download the News24 app for Android or iPhone. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter  